
[1]swath

   SWATH, n. swoth.

   1. A line of grass or grain cut and thrown together by the sythe in
   mowing or cradling.

   2. The whole breadth or sweep of a sythe in mowing or cradling; as a
   wide swath.

   3. A band or fillet. They wrapped me in a hundred yards of swath.
